text: Conservatives in blue, Labour in red and Liberal Democrats in yellow. Wards in dark grey were not contested in 2003. The 2003 Swale Borough Council election took place on 1 May 2003 to elect members of Swale Borough Council in Kent, England. One third of the council was up for election and the Conservative party stayed in overall control of the council. After the election, the composition of the council was *Conservative 25 *Labour 11 *Liberal Democrats 11 ==Election result== ==Ward results== ==References== 2003 Category:2003 English local elections Category:2000s in Kent
